=========================================================
Why do we need the base function?
=========================================================

Base function

void log()
{
    cout<<"Base Function";
}

terminates the recursion.

Without it,

log(args...)

would keep calling itself forever.

Eventually compiler won't find a matching function
when no arguments remain.

Compilation Error.

